Erasmus' present purpose in going to Antwerp was perhaps to throw off the effects of his recent illness (see p. 283). He stayed no doubt with the ever hospitable Gilles. Either on this occasion, or when he was at Antwerp again in August (p. 324), he received a visit from two delegate-s sent by the Bohemian Bfethren (Ep. 1021. 95n), who were commissioned to show him a copy of the Apoloyz'a for their position composed by themselves in 1507, and to ask for bis· opinion of it.
